                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1718" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             wrote, and some Nugent wrote. I wrote one myself; John Folkard accepted it, and he accepted Bond's, and he accepted one in black ink; he gave that to the Baroness to get another person.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you remember any thing being said about these stamps - A. Nugent asked 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1719">
                  William 
                  Folkard
               <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1719" type="surname" value="Folkard"></interp>
