                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1720" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came out and told us there was no room there. He took us to the White Bear. I saw 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1721">
                  John 
                  Folkard
               <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1721" type="surname" value="Folkard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1721" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1721" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             there. Nugent came afterwards. Bond, Shehey, and Kelly were there, and before we went to Guildhall the bills were arrayed and looked to by 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1722">
                  William 
                  Folkard
               <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1722" type="surname" value="Folkard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1722" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1722" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , to see that they were all right.</p>
               <p>Q. Did you go to Guildhall - A. I did, and proved the debt. After that I went back to the White Bear with Bond. I then saw Nugent and the other parties there, John and 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1723">
                  William 
                  Folkard
               <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1723" type="surname" value="Folkard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1723" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1723" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Nugent took the bills of me and Bond. He gave me a one-pound note.</p>
               <p>Q. Afterwards did Mr. Powis, the assignee, come and make enquiry about your debt - A. I saw Mr. Powis at Bond's.</p>
               <p>Q. After Mr. Powis came and questioned you about your debt, do you remember John Folkard came and wrote any papers for you - A. He wrote that paper for me in case Mr. Powis came there again. I asked John Folkard what I was to do about the business. He said, he would give me an account, and at the same time he wrote Mr. Bond's.</p>
