                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1729" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. You lived as servant with the Baroness in February last - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you recollect on the Sunday, shortly after you were there, your mistress and Mrs. Bond going out - A. Yes, and they came home in the evening about eleven o'clock. Before they came home, Mr. Nugent and the two Folkards called and left a note. They said, they should call again. Mr. Nugent gave me the note. I gave it to my mistress. After my mistress came, Nugent and the two Folkards came. They went into my mistres's room. Some liquor was sent for. One of the Folkards was writing on paper. There was something like a stamp upon it. I do not know one of the Folkards from the other.</p>
               <p>JOB POPE. I keep a green-grocer's shop, in Greek-street, Red-lion-square.</p>
               <p>Q. Did the prisoner Nugent live in your house - A. He did, about a twelvemonth ago last 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1730">August. At</persName>
             the time he was with me he was very poor. He has borrowed one, two, and three shillings of me. He had a wife and one child.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120916-214-person1731">
                  JONATHAN 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1731" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1731" type="given" value="JONATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1731" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a victualler.</p>
               <p>Q. Do you know Nugent - A. Yes, for about a twelvemonth. He got in my debt for porter about thirteen shillings. He paid me five shillings off. He said, he would call and pay the remainder. He never did.</p>
               <p>JOHN NAARY. I am a dealer in coals. Nugent lived opposite of me. He is in debt five shillings and sixpence to me now for a sack of coals.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="181209160107"></xptr> CATHERINE MORANDA. Q. Before the month of January last did you know 
               <persName id="t18120916-214-person1732">
                  John 
                  Folkard
