                     <interp inst="t18120916-214-person1732" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , who lived in Blackfriars-road, a silversmith - A. I do not know any thing about him. I never received any goods or bill of him.</p>
               <p>Q. The charge is one hundred and sixty pounds nine shillings, for different articles - A. I never had any goods of him, nor never had any conversation with the Baroness about Mr. Folkard.</p>
               <p>COURT. The counsel gives up the prosecution against Humphreys and James Folkard.</p>

